   "body" : "When using connect command line function it opens two connections to the IP specified...\n\n09/27/12 17:32:31 accepted connection xx:22348\n09/27/12 17:32:31 accepted connection xx:22347\n\nIt also continues to open connections up to your maximum # of outgoing connections rather than\nthe stated \"Connect only to the specified node(s)\".  The double connection is counted as 1, so if you have the default max of 8 outgoing connections, it'll open 7 more.  It doesn't allow incoming connections.\n\nobserved behavior in bitcoin-qt and bitcoind (windows)",
